title: API Reference Documentation
extracted_text: API Reference Documentation. Overview. This document provides comprehensive information about the vox API endpoints and their usage. Authentication. All API requests require authentication using an API key. Session Management API. The session management API allows you to programmatically save, load, list, and delete reading sessions. POST /api/sessions - Create a new session. GET /api/sessions - List all sessions. GET /api/sessions/:name - Get session details. DELETE /api/sessions/:name - Delete a session. Playback Control API. The playback control API provides endpoints for managing audio playback state. POST /api/playback/pause - Pause current playback. POST /api/playback/resume - Resume paused playback. POST /api/playback/seek - Seek to specific position. Text-to-Speech API. The TTS API enables on-demand synthesis of text content. POST /api/tts/synthesize - Synthesize text to speech. GET /api/tts/voices - List available voices.
